<br />
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><br />
This deck i built while writing an article about Consorting With Wizards, and i think it works pretty well.  If you read the article, which you should to fully understand the Free Peoples side, you&#39;ll see that I use card drawing through Red Book and Town Center, plus twilight choke through Consorting With Wizards, plus Hobbit powerhouses like my invincible base 6 str Bilbo.  I protect my Hobbit tales with Pippin, my Hobbit allies with Nice Imitation, and I still manage to get a lot of condition discarding in to screw over most decks with Bilbo and Athelas.  Plus my Fellowship is pretty strong.<br />
<br />
On the Moria side, a 49 card half-deck looks pretty dang cool....and it lets me dig forever to get my minions out.  I have both of the Balrog&#39;s weapons in here, even though it&#39;s dang hard to get them both on him, at least i&#39;m thinking that way.  even without the big hurt, i&#39;ve got a pretty snazzy weapon-oriented swarm deck that seems to get the job done.  especially since my Fellowship tends to choke their hand with shadow cards so they can&#39;t get the ones they need before my goblins come knockin&#39;.<br />
<br />
Check it out, i kind of built it on a lark and it looks pretty cool.  i&#39;m not too concerned about the decksize since i&#39;ve to so many discarding and drawing techniques, but if you think its a problem, give me a list of cards that you think aren&#39;t pulling their weight...because i think just about every one of them is worth the slot.  anyway, thanks for reviewing, please try to be constructive in your comments.<br />
<br />
<br />
Ryan French<br />
Rebel Fellowship founder<br />
